        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The Department of Distance &amp;amp; Education, School of Open Learning, Campus of Open Learning (DDCE/SOL/COL), in the spirit of facilitating financially weak students as per guidelines decided by the University of Delhi, has announced the Financial Support Scheme for DDCE/SOL/COL students. This scheme is reflected through a fee waiver/refund for the students enrolled in DDCE/SOL/COL and having their family income below the poverty line. The fee waiver/refund includes all components of the fee paid by students except the examination fee and the university fee.\n<br>\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "<br>\n\n**S. No.****Family income (in ₹) per annum****Fee waiver (percentage)****Remarks**Category 1Less than or equal to ₹ 4,00,000/Up to 100%Actual fee or up to a maximum of ₹ 15000/-Category 2Between ₹ 4,00,000/- and ₹ 8,00,000/-Up to 50%Actual fee or up to a maximum of ₹ 10,000/-<br>\n\n",
        "exclusions_md": "\n  - 2nd, 3rd &amp;amp; 4th year candidates with ER/Arrears of previous examination papers are not eligible to apply.\n<br>\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme aims to provide financial assistance to financially weak students of the University of Delhi to help them overcome financial challenges and continue their education without hardship.",
